Na5 12. cxb6 (12. Nd2 Bxg2 13. Kxg2 {Schmidt,J (2265)-Shmirina,E (2164)
Dresden 2003 (1-0, 37)} d6 14. cxd6 cxd6 15. Bb4 Nc6 16. Nc4 d5 $1 $15 {
Black consolidates his control over the light squares and can dream with an
ending with a good knight versus a bad bishop already. If} 17. Nd6 $2 Re7 18.
Nb5 Rb7 $19 {[%cal Ga7a6] followed by ...a7-a6. White cannot avoid material
